<br>
I enjoy a good fantasy novel. My first was (of course) The Lord of the Rings, wich I have read about 6 times now (I know I am weird) one of them loud for my son when he was around 8 years old. But there are others too, and two not so well known are my personal favourites.<br>
<br>
&quot;Memory, Sorrow and Thorn&quot; a trilogy by Tad Williams. It's a great fantasy adventure in a classic mold, but the persons are much more complex than in most novels. The evil ones are not purely evil and the good ones are sometimes very human too. And they die. Not only the bad guys at the end, but the ones you like too. Not all of course, it's not that unique  =)<br>
