 His &quot;Prey&quot; books are not fantasy like most of the books on my list. These are ... well I'm too tired to remember the name of the genre, but they are about a Minneapolis homocide cop if that helps with the classification. Very suspenseful and complex. Written under the pseudonym John Sandford by pulitzer prize winning journalist John Camp, and worth a read if you get tired of fantasy or just want something different.<br>
<br>
  J. R. R. Tolkien<br>
 If you are playing EQ and haven't read &quot;The Hobbit&quot; or &quot;Lord of the Rings&quot; there must be something wrong. These are the books that started it all for most fantasy readers.<br>
<br>
